  "response": "Money laundering is typically defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Legal definitions usually involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the money into legitimate economic channels\n\nThe specific legal details can vary between jurisdictions, but generally involve intentional attempts to hide the origins of money from criminal activities.",
